Scrape the cheese and toppings off the pizza crust, it may help to heat the pizza in the microwave. Discard the crust. Heat the toppings and milk in a small saucepan over medium heat. Stir until the topping and milk combine, it should be a soft clumpy consistency. Remove from the heat. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat. Whisk the eggs, Italian seasoning, onion powder, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Pour in eggs and cook without stirring for 1 minute. Add the pizza toppings to the eggs; cook, stirring constantly, until eggs reach the desired consistency.